Challenge 8 • Stretch Challenge
AutoSpec: Al Agent That Writes Its Own Spec, Builds, and Tests
A multi-agent pipeline that takes a plain English brief and autonomously produces a spec, working code, and a passing test suite — end to end.
PERSONA
A product manager at a software consultancy who needs to rapidly prototype client ideas. They can describe what they want in plain English but have no engineering background. They want to hand a two-paragraph brief to an Al system and receive back a deployable prototype - with requirements documented, code written, and tests passing - ready to demo to the client the same day.
INPUTS
*   Plain English product brief (2-3 sentences)
*   Acceptance criteria hints
*   Tech stack preference (Python/Node)
*   Quality threshold config (test coverage %)
WHAT TO BUILD (USING KIRO)
Use Kiro to design and orchestrate a pipeline of at least three specialised agents: a Spec Agent (converts the brief into structured requirements and acceptance criteria), a Build Agent (generates code from the spec), and a Test Agent (writes and runs unit tests against the code, reporting pass/fail). A fourth Review Agent that checks spec-to-code alignment is the bonus challenge. The pipeline should be triggered by a single input and produce all artefacts without human intervention mid-run.
OUTPUTS & DELIVERABLES
*   Live end-to-end pipeline demo
*   Generated spec document (sample run)
*   Agent handoff diagram
*   Kiro spec + agent orchestration design
*   Generated code + passing test results
*   3-min pitch




	
