About AWS Kiro
Kiro is AWS's agentic Al IDE that helps you go from prototype to production using spec-driven development. Instead of jumping straight to code, you describe what you want to build in plain English - Kiro turns that into a structured spec with requirements and acceptance criteria, then generates working code, documentation, and tests automatically.
For this hackathon, Kiro is your team's main tool. Use it to:
*   Write your initial product brief and let Kiro generate the spec
*   Scaffold code from the spec with Al agents
*   Auto-generate unit tests and documentation
*   Iterate quickly using Kiro's steering files to guide style and conventions
